  "body": " Let be a finite group of order , and prime. By , has a nontrivial center. Since the center of any group is a normal subgroup, cannot be a simple group. Therefore, groups of orders , , , , , , , , , and are not simple. In fact, the groups of order , , , and are abelian by .  "
