  "body": "  Let be a commutative ring with identity , where . Then is a prime ideal in if and only if is an integral domain.    First let us assume that is an ideal in and is an integral domain. Suppose that . If and are two elements of such that , then either or . This means that either is in or is in , which shows that must be prime.  Conversely, suppose that is prime and . Then . If , then must be in by the definition of a prime ideal; hence, and is an integral domain.   "
